4🔹 repartition vs coalesce

### Explanation

“repartition increases or decreases partitions with full shuffle, while coalesce reduces partitions without shuffle, making it more efficient for decreasing partitions.”

### Code

```python
rdd = spark.sparkContext.parallelize(range(10), 4)

rdd2 = rdd.repartition(6)
rdd3 = rdd.coalesce(2)
```

### Why it matters

Controls parallelism and performance tuning.

