## 🔹 When to use RDD over DataFrame

### Explanation

“RDDs are used when low-level transformations or fine-grained control is required, especially for unstructured data, while DataFrames are preferred for optimized structured processing.”

### Code

```python
rdd = spark.sparkContext.parallelize(["a b", "c d"])
print(rdd.flatMap(lambda x: x.split()).collect())
```

### Why it matters

Gives control where optimization is not required.

