## 🔹 Partitioning in RDD

### Explanation

“Partitioning in RDD refers to how data is divided across nodes, which directly affects parallelism and performance.”

### Code

```python
rdd = spark.sparkContext.parallelize(range(10), 3)
print(rdd.getNumPartitions())
```

### Why it matters

Directly impacts execution speed.

